<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Gimbok the Ogre on 11-04-2001 10:02 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Muse,
  I've been playing EQ for over a year now, and have consecutively given up on characters because I didn't know where to go, would get killed while lost, etc.  Gimbok is one of the 3rd-level chars who was in limbo for the last 8 months, until I found out about eqatlas.com a few months ago.  It's revolutionized my game play!
  Thanks to your maps, I have been much more successful in my explorations, and I've been reactivating old characters now that I know there are some interesting places near them where I won't die (don't ask how long Gimbok spent wandering Ogre city and the Feerrott - he was subsequently banished to limbo until my EQatlas epiphany).  I'm glad to see how much everyone appreciates your maps, and I hope Verant does, as well.
    In regard to your situation, there are two pieces that I think would revolutionize your perspective without us paying to (yet another) pay site.  

1)  There are SO many people who enjoy wandering to new places and seeing what's there.  Have us help you with the mapping (you don't have to do all of it - have a list of what you need done, and we'll run with it!).

2)  When I drive through several states, I buy maps that I can refer to along the way.  It seems ludicrous to me that the same does not exist in the realm of Norrath!  What would make the most sense is for my ogre shammy to be able to purchase maps from shopkeepers (namely, your maps but now inside the EQ world instead of on a separate website).  I'm thinking two pieces of this: a map book for sale, and then you buy the individual map pages in the various zones.  For ogres in Oggok, they probably wouldn't see a lot of Surefall maps.  For rangers in Surefall, they wouldn't see a lot of Guk maps.  But when they saw one for sale (or loot), they could add it to their map book.
   This removes your need to maintain the website (but not the generation of maps), removes Verant's argument about the spoilers, and removes the need for this to be a pay site (if you could convince Verant to pay you well for this, for which I'm sure you would have a huge backing from we the players).  

Best of luck in your endeavors, and keep enjoying everything you do!

Gimbok the Ogre
9th-level Shaman</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
